article.description: Joshua Braun scored 20 points and Grand Canyon handled Texas-Rio Grande Valley 83-63 in the Western Athletic Conference opener for both teams on Thursday.
article.headline: Grand Canyon handles Texas-Rio Grande Valley 83-63
article.linkText: Grand Canyon handles Texas-Rio Grande Valley 83-63
article.story: PHOENIX -- Joshua Braun scored 20 points and Grand Canyon handled Texas-Rio Grande Valley 83-63 in the Western Athletic Conference opener for both teams on Thursday. Braun was 7 of 13 from the floor, with six 3-pointers. The Antelopes (14-2) made 10 of 25 from beyond the arc. Grandy Glaze scored 17 points with 12 rebounds, and Dominic Magee added 14 points. Grand Canyon dominated the boards, 45-27. UT-Rio Grande Valley (4-12) was led by Dakota Slaughter with 15 points, while Shaquille Hines and Dan Kimasa both added 14. Grand Canyon made an 11-point run early -- including a pair of 3s by Braun -- and led 45-28 at the break. Braun's 3-pointer with 8:19 left made it 69-51, and the lead reached 20 with 6:34 to go on a Magee 3-pointer. Rio Grande Valley didn't make a basket over the final 3:24.
